Former 'Backstage' actor Sibusiso Radebe. JOHANNESBURG - Former star of popular e.tv drama Backstage Sibusiso Radebe has died aged 37. His manager Wesley Gainer confirmed the news in a statement on Friday. READ: Tributes pour in for veteran actress Nomhle Nkonyeni "We are all still in shock and not in the right space to comment. At this stage, we feel the family reserves the right to speak when they ready', said Gainer. Radebe is well-known for his role as Vusi on Backstage. He was also a presenter on SABC 1 children's show YoTV. Twitter is being flooded with messages of condolence.